WEBVTT

00:04.630 --> 00:05.959
Done yet?

00:06.131 --> 00:07.413
Done yet?

00:07.591 --> 00:09.668
Your books
are an unmitigated disaster.

00:09.885 --> 00:11.546
- I haven't even begun.
- No hurry.

00:11.720 --> 00:13.050
Take your time.

00:13.764 --> 00:17.348
I was up planning the senior sleigh ride
and now I can't find my backpack.

00:17.518 --> 00:20.555
It's right here
where you left it 12 hours ago,

00:20.729 --> 00:23.019
which begs the question,
did you do any homework?

00:23.232 --> 00:24.513
Did I mention I managed to book

00:24.691 --> 00:27.183
an entire team of Clydesdales
and mull cider?

00:27.402 --> 00:29.313
Sabrina,
you know homework comes first.

00:29.530 --> 00:31.523
Unless it's something icky
like bookkeeping.

00:31.698 --> 00:33.526
Come on, I'm 18.
I can vote in two realms.

00:33.742 --> 00:35.736
I can be in charge of organising
my own schedule.

00:35.911 --> 00:39.779
I'm sorry, but if you live under our roof,
you live under our rules.

00:41.291 --> 00:43.830
Oh, Lord, I've swallowed Mother.

00:44.461 --> 00:45.743
Fine.

00:46.547 --> 00:49.216
Your stupid roof, your stupid rules.

00:56.932 --> 00:59.471
Oh, the frigid wind of teen rebellion.

00:59.643 --> 01:01.518
Oh, look, the blimp.

01:03.000 --> 01:09.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:40.642 --> 01:43.181
Everyone's talking about
how cool the sleigh ride's gonna be.

01:43.395 --> 01:46.064
Oh, it's great, but did anyone offer
to do my calculus homework?

01:46.773 --> 01:49.443
You know, sugar-induced comas
aren't all they're cracked up to be.

01:49.651 --> 01:51.396
Last night, coach made a new rule.

01:51.570 --> 01:56.363
Only three sodas a week, I reached
my quota before he finished talking.

01:56.575 --> 01:59.067
I'm sure it was the carbonation
he objected to.

01:59.244 --> 02:00.739
There you are. I was getting worried.

02:00.913 --> 02:03.784
- Do you have the article?
- Almost. I just have to write it down.

02:03.999 --> 02:05.957
But the deadline is 9 tonight.

02:06.126 --> 02:10.291
If you're not ready, I can always run
that profile of our AFS student, Grindl.

02:10.506 --> 02:13.294
No, I have a great headline story.
I'll get it to you by press time.

02:13.467 --> 02:16.635
Well, going against everything
that I stand for in gut.

02:16.803 --> 02:18.263
Okay.

02:18.764 --> 02:20.259
I'm working today
at the coffeehouse.

02:20.432 --> 02:22.011
I'll have all the time to finish it.

02:25.479 --> 02:28.101
Just my luck. Everyone in Westbridge
must've read the news item:

02:28.273 --> 02:30.433
Caffeine makes you live longer.

02:33.862 --> 02:37.065
I either bury this sweater
or learn how to knit.

02:37.241 --> 02:38.321
Bury.

02:38.534 --> 02:41.239
What's this? Sparkly, warm.

02:41.453 --> 02:45.582
Mother of mercy,
it's a flake of magic.

02:46.875 --> 02:49.367
One small French Roast, 75 cents.

02:50.379 --> 02:52.503
What are you doing?
You can't just give stuff away.

02:52.714 --> 02:55.253
Oh, he paid for the coffee,
I just gave him some free foam.

02:55.425 --> 02:57.134
We've got lots.

02:57.302 --> 02:58.383
Surprisingly,

02:58.554 --> 03:01.093
businesses are very touchy
about giving stuff away for free.

03:01.306 --> 03:02.422
You could get suspended.

03:02.599 --> 03:04.972
Okay, I really don't do it that often.

03:05.143 --> 03:07.600
No, that's okay.
I'm gonna wait for her.

03:10.983 --> 03:14.483
Salem, there is not a vein of magic
running under the house.

03:14.653 --> 03:18.237
It's probably just some leftover
magic dust from centuries of spells.

03:18.407 --> 03:20.068
She's right. Every spring cleaning,

03:20.242 --> 03:23.493
I'm covered with enough sparkle
to skate with Oksana Baiul.

03:23.704 --> 03:25.614
But go ahead
and use your little spark.

03:25.831 --> 03:26.994
Stand back.

03:27.165 --> 03:29.740
<i>I found magic through a legal route</i>

03:29.918 --> 03:33.668
<i>Help me get the rest of the loot</i>

03:33.839 --> 03:37.042
Jedediah Orenstein,
magic prospector at your service.

03:37.259 --> 03:40.380
SALEM:
Yahoo! Let's go dig for magic.

03:41.096 --> 03:42.176
I would have bet money

03:42.347 --> 03:44.721
that he would have conjured up
a snow-cone machine.

03:46.768 --> 03:48.513
We're screening <i>The Godfather</i>
here tonight.

03:48.687 --> 03:49.767
You coming?

03:49.938 --> 03:52.857
[IN GODFATHER VOICE]
Oh, that is an offer I can't refuse.

03:53.066 --> 03:54.727
Oh, I didn't know
you could do Cary Grant.

03:54.943 --> 03:56.024
It starts at 9.

03:56.486 --> 03:59.654
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Oh, but my curfew's at 10.

03:59.823 --> 04:01.947
Oh, man, a curfew. That's cute.

04:02.159 --> 04:05.362
Hey, you know, it's a part of my deal
with my parole officer.

04:05.954 --> 04:08.078
Please, just extend it to 11:30?

04:08.290 --> 04:10.996
- You blew the roof off this morning.
- It was a joke.

04:11.168 --> 04:13.742
And we already extended
your curfew for the sleigh ride.

04:14.630 --> 04:15.710
Fine.

04:15.881 --> 04:18.966
I'll just watch enough of <i>The Godfather</i>
to think it's a feel-good movie.

04:20.010 --> 04:24.388
I know it was a long, long time ago,
but were we rebellious teens?

04:24.598 --> 04:29.060
No way. We were too busy
gathering posies to ward off the plague.

04:35.609 --> 04:38.860
You're gonna write your article and do
your homework during the movie?

04:39.029 --> 04:41.153
Yeah, how distracting
can a Mafia family be?

04:41.323 --> 04:43.530
[GUNFIRE & TYRES SCREECHING]

04:47.079 --> 04:48.657
Nothing but dirt.

04:48.872 --> 04:50.996
You gotta have patience.

04:51.208 --> 04:54.909
I remember back
in the magic rush of 1414,

04:55.087 --> 04:56.962
it took weeks before I struck it rich.

04:57.172 --> 04:58.751
What happened to all your magic?

04:58.966 --> 05:00.509
Typical story.

05:00.676 --> 05:04.425
Racehorses, showgirls, mahjongg.

05:05.931 --> 05:08.138
Salem, I think we struck.

05:08.976 --> 05:11.100
SALEM:
Ugh! Argh!

05:13.939 --> 05:16.182
A sewage line.

05:16.358 --> 05:17.687
[SOBS]

05:17.860 --> 05:21.693
I should have gotten
a snow-cone machine.

05:22.447 --> 05:27.157
Finally, I have brought order
to the chaos of Hilda's clock shop.

05:28.453 --> 05:29.617
Found these under my bed.

05:29.830 --> 05:31.989
Oh, great.

05:32.165 --> 05:35.785
More receipts. And a sock.

05:40.257 --> 05:41.337
Coach was right.

05:41.508 --> 05:44.676
I've never felt more alive
since I switched to water.

05:44.845 --> 05:46.506
I haven't even finished a paragraph.

05:46.722 --> 05:49.261
We've been here for two hours.
Maybe some water would help.

05:49.474 --> 05:51.302
Two hours? It's after 10.

05:51.768 --> 05:53.561
- I'm dead.
- You're dead.

05:53.729 --> 05:56.435
Get home now. No more excuses.

05:58.567 --> 06:00.228
But...

06:02.738 --> 06:07.199
Besides breaking curfew,
there's another little matter.

06:07.367 --> 06:09.160
QUICK [ON MACHINE]:
<i>Hello, this is Mrs. Quick.</i>

06:09.369 --> 06:11.197
<i>I have a message for Sabrina.</i>

06:11.413 --> 06:14.949
[IN ANGRY TONE] <i>Where
the blue blazes is your article?</i>

06:15.125 --> 06:17.748
[IN NICE TONE]
<i>Sorry to disturb you at home.</i>

06:18.545 --> 06:21.547
Well, I have one thing to say
about Mrs. Quick:

06:21.757 --> 06:23.549
I'm guessing
you haven't done your homework.

06:23.717 --> 06:25.378
No, I was going to
right after I got home.

06:25.552 --> 06:27.261
I mean,
right after I typed up my article.

06:27.429 --> 06:29.637
Sabrina, Hilda is right.

06:29.806 --> 06:32.133
You're dead.
You are grounded for a week.

06:32.351 --> 06:35.353
- But...
- That means no sleigh ride.

06:35.521 --> 06:36.601
No sleigh ride.

06:36.772 --> 06:38.018
Really?

06:38.232 --> 06:39.941
Oh, come on.
I'm just hurting myself here.

06:41.276 --> 06:44.148
Oh, I'm really starting to hate rules.

06:44.363 --> 06:45.443
No sleigh ride?

06:46.907 --> 06:49.066
Do you really think
I like being the disciplinarian?

06:49.284 --> 06:51.741
- Kind of.
- Well, for your information,

06:51.912 --> 06:55.661
I would much rather be out
singing and dancing.

06:55.874 --> 06:58.413
With William Bennett
and George Will.

07:03.799 --> 07:05.627
Can't believe you can't go
on the sleigh ride.

07:05.843 --> 07:07.635
I was up half the night.
I was so excited.

07:07.845 --> 07:09.423
No, because you were
amped up on sugar.

07:09.596 --> 07:13.262
You'd better be careful,
if that stuff wears off, you could crash.

07:17.020 --> 07:19.144
Well, thank you very much.

07:19.815 --> 07:22.983
And the Grindl story
came with photos.

07:23.610 --> 07:25.900
Mrs. Quick, wait...

07:26.780 --> 07:29.782
Loitering and littering.

07:36.832 --> 07:38.244
I swear, this claim is drier

07:38.417 --> 07:40.161
than Macon County
on a Sunday morning.

07:40.377 --> 07:44.079
Just keep digging,
sourdough breath.

07:44.923 --> 07:48.376
You know,
I'm getting plumb tired of taking orders

07:48.552 --> 07:52.004
from a talking gerbil
who's got more fleas than brains.

07:52.598 --> 07:56.596
Says the yokel who hasn't bathed
since the McKinley administration.

07:56.810 --> 08:00.761
- Why, you little...
- You're going down-- Ah!

08:03.150 --> 08:04.728
[RUMBLING]

08:04.943 --> 08:06.439
More sewage.

08:08.739 --> 08:10.234
- It's magic.
- We're rich.

08:10.407 --> 08:12.484
- We've struck magic.
- We're rich.

08:14.411 --> 08:15.527
JEDEDIAH:
I'll get you.

08:15.704 --> 08:17.863
Can't go on the sleigh ride,
I'm grounded for a week,

08:18.040 --> 08:20.247
I screwed up the paper,
and my teacher is mad at me.

08:20.417 --> 08:22.292
Excuse me, this is a little bland.

08:22.461 --> 08:25.831
- Could I get an extra shot of vanilla?
- Oh, yeah, sure.

08:26.006 --> 08:29.257
Anyway, on the positive side,
at least things can't get any worse.

08:29.426 --> 08:32.428
Sabrina,
you cannot give away free syrup.

08:32.596 --> 08:35.217
I can't believe I have to say this,
but you're suspended.

08:38.227 --> 08:42.390
Take my advice. Never ever,
ever say things can't get worse.

08:46.109 --> 08:47.688
Why, you look gloomier

08:47.903 --> 08:50.477
than a one-legged dog
at a tap-dance recital.

08:50.697 --> 08:52.940
Well, thanks to everyone's rules,
I'm stuck in my room,

08:53.116 --> 08:55.869
I've lost my job, and I'm being
compared to a crippled canine.

08:56.745 --> 08:58.288
I wanna be in charge of my own life.

08:58.497 --> 08:59.957
Well, it sounds like you need to go

09:00.123 --> 09:02.283
to a place
where you get to make the rules.

09:02.459 --> 09:05.794
But I'm too old for Chuck E. Cheese
and I can't afford my own island.

09:05.963 --> 09:08.040
I know a good place for you to go.

09:19.268 --> 09:21.427
I'm almost positive
this isn't my room.

09:33.365 --> 09:35.939
So this is the old coot's idea
of an ideal vacation.

09:36.118 --> 09:39.239
I guess he couldn't book me
at Club Med Rwanda.

09:39.413 --> 09:42.450
See how they like it when they don't
have somebody to enforce the law.

09:42.624 --> 09:45.199
- I swear, the first person I run into--
- Aunt Zelda?

09:45.377 --> 09:47.121
Congratulations.

09:47.296 --> 09:48.921
- You're the new sheriff.
- Ow!

09:49.131 --> 09:50.377
I'm sick of being the boss.

09:50.549 --> 09:52.922
It's up to you now. Good luck.

09:53.677 --> 09:56.169
With what?
The job or cauterising the wound?

09:56.388 --> 09:58.631
Now I can do
what I've always wanted to do.

09:58.807 --> 10:01.975
Rise to the highest position
a woman can rise to.

10:02.144 --> 10:03.390
Dance-hall girl.

10:03.562 --> 10:04.761
Call me Frenchy.

10:08.775 --> 10:10.105
Aunt Frenchy?

10:12.070 --> 10:13.151
Howdy, partners.

10:13.363 --> 10:15.357
It's okay, everyone.
Go back to your bridge games.

10:15.532 --> 10:16.909
- Just the sheriff.
- Aunt Hilda?

10:17.117 --> 10:19.277
Miss Hildie. I own the place.

10:19.453 --> 10:21.245
Welcome to the Wild West.

10:21.413 --> 10:22.873
It looks more like the Sedate West.

10:23.040 --> 10:26.457
Well, we try to live
by a few simple guidelines.

10:28.086 --> 10:31.290
Wow, that's a lot of rules.
No water before 10 a.m.?

10:31.507 --> 10:32.966
We only have one bathroom.

10:33.175 --> 10:36.343
Excuse me, who coughed
without covering their mouth?

10:36.512 --> 10:38.422
Who broke number 52?

10:38.597 --> 10:39.677
Wait.

10:39.848 --> 10:41.474
You think that no-water rule
is tough?

10:41.683 --> 10:43.344
You should see number 143.

10:43.519 --> 10:45.512
No sarsaparilla, ever.

10:45.729 --> 10:47.853
And yet there's no rule
against silly hats?

10:48.065 --> 10:49.643
I'm Deputy Fizz.

10:49.816 --> 10:51.857
If there's anything you need
for me to do, just...

10:52.402 --> 10:55.321
Oh, it's my turn for the bathroom.

10:55.489 --> 10:58.158
Can someone please explain to me
what's going on here?

10:58.325 --> 11:00.615
Quickdraw's the name,
editing is my game.

11:00.786 --> 11:03.194
I know everything there is to know
about this town.

11:04.581 --> 11:06.290
Thanks. You've been a big help.

11:07.125 --> 11:10.127
All you need to know is,
it's your job to enforce the rules.

11:10.295 --> 11:12.004
And you make all the rules.

11:12.214 --> 11:14.504
Oh, well, in that case...

11:15.217 --> 11:17.009
Hey, no standing on chairs.

11:17.219 --> 11:18.798
- Josh?
- Don't know him.

11:18.971 --> 11:21.095
- You could check the bathroom.
- Never mind.

11:21.682 --> 11:24.256
As sheriff,
I'm adding a new rule to the list.

11:24.476 --> 11:25.556
Of course you are.

11:25.727 --> 11:28.184
Ten seconds, and the power
goes straight to their head.

11:28.355 --> 11:30.514
The new rule is, there are no rules.

11:30.732 --> 11:32.560
[CROWD CHEERING]

11:32.734 --> 11:34.562
How about a song, Frenchy?

11:34.778 --> 11:37.151
[SINGING] <i>Camp town ladies
Sing this song</i>

11:37.364 --> 11:39.192
<i>Doodah, doodah</i>

11:39.408 --> 11:41.532
And sarsaparillas are on the house.

11:42.494 --> 11:44.287
Sheriff, I think I love you.

11:47.583 --> 11:49.541
I think I'm gonna like this place.

12:18.947 --> 12:20.822
Three cheers for the new sheriff.

12:20.991 --> 12:22.190
[CROWD CHEERING]

12:22.367 --> 12:24.610
I love this town
and I love all you people.

12:24.828 --> 12:27.403
Trouble's coming.

12:27.623 --> 12:30.708
Trouble's coming.

12:30.918 --> 12:33.207
- What?
- The Petulant Kid.

12:33.879 --> 12:35.255
[CROWD GASP]

12:35.422 --> 12:38.874
On the next train.
It's due in one hour.

12:40.969 --> 12:43.544
I guess that's what happens
when they cut local taxes.

12:43.722 --> 12:45.098
Well, who is this Petulant Kid?

12:46.141 --> 12:48.680
Why do you keep doing that
when I say Petulant Kid?

12:48.894 --> 12:52.430
- Knock it off.
- Hey, the sheriff will handle this.

12:52.606 --> 12:54.267
Anybody wanna go play
with matches?

12:54.483 --> 12:55.682
CROWD:
Yeah.

12:55.859 --> 12:57.853
- Wait, wait, what's going on?
- Forget it.

12:58.028 --> 13:00.734
My days of spitting out information
on demand are over.

13:00.906 --> 13:02.366
This is your problem now.

13:02.533 --> 13:03.814
Dibs on the lighter fluid.

13:04.034 --> 13:06.407
Problem? Why is everyone
so worried about this kid?

13:06.620 --> 13:08.329
CAT:
Oh, boy.

13:08.497 --> 13:10.407
Thanks.

13:10.582 --> 13:12.042
Wait a minute.

13:12.209 --> 13:15.626
Billy the Kid. The Sundance Kid.

13:15.963 --> 13:18.087
Hopefully,
I'm just jumping to conclusions.

13:19.550 --> 13:22.587
I'll check the wanted posters
in the sheriff's office.

13:26.723 --> 13:27.804
MAN:
Excuse me, miss?

13:28.016 --> 13:30.555
Do you know how many years
I have left on my sentence?

13:30.769 --> 13:32.430
Mr. Kraft?

13:32.646 --> 13:35.518
- No, they call me Sweet Will.
- Let me guess.

13:35.691 --> 13:36.854
You run the local schoolhouse

13:37.025 --> 13:39.315
and you're locked up
for torturing high schoolers.

13:40.070 --> 13:43.939
Oh, no, I blocked an alley
with my chuck waggon.

13:44.157 --> 13:46.484
- And?
- And got caught.

13:46.952 --> 13:49.325
You know, I finally get awful
Mr. Kraft behind bars

13:49.538 --> 13:51.864
and he turns out
to be the nicest guy in town.

13:52.040 --> 13:53.121
So everyone says.

13:53.333 --> 13:55.576
Well, blocking an alley
with a chuck waggon is up there

13:55.752 --> 13:58.209
with giving an extra shot of vanilla.

13:58.422 --> 14:00.131
Yes.

14:00.841 --> 14:05.967
Oh, may your life be filled
with happiness.

14:06.180 --> 14:08.173
Oh, maybe they should call you
Saccharine Will.

14:09.224 --> 14:13.140
Hey, by any chance, do you know
anything about the Petulant--?

14:14.188 --> 14:16.015
Okay, that is getting really annoying.

14:16.231 --> 14:17.691
CAT:
Lock me up, please.

14:17.858 --> 14:21.442
I'm terrified of the Petulant Kid.

14:21.653 --> 14:23.943
Tell me about this kid
or you're a tennis racket.

14:24.114 --> 14:25.194
Five, four--

14:25.365 --> 14:30.278
The biggest, orneriest, no-goodnik
this side of the Rio Grande.

14:30.495 --> 14:34.411
The Petulant Kid's goal
is to destroy authority,

14:34.583 --> 14:38.498
and since you're the authority,
well, you can do the math.

14:38.712 --> 14:41.584
But I don't wanna be the authority.

14:44.468 --> 14:45.548
Wait a minute.

14:45.719 --> 14:47.380
There is only one of him
and dozens of us.

14:47.554 --> 14:49.097
I'll just get everyone to help.

14:49.598 --> 14:52.304
So I say, one for all and all for one.
Are you with me?

14:52.518 --> 14:54.096
No way.

14:55.604 --> 14:57.930
[SINGING] <i>As he was walking
Down the street</i>

14:58.106 --> 15:00.314
<i>Down the street, down the street</i>

15:00.484 --> 15:02.477
<i>The pretty little maiden
He chanced to meet</i>

15:02.653 --> 15:03.982
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING]

15:04.154 --> 15:05.400
- Is that the train?
- No.

15:05.572 --> 15:08.491
That's the whistle that tells us
the train will be here in 15 minutes.

15:08.700 --> 15:12.070
Well, I guess there's only
one thing left to do. Beg.

15:12.246 --> 15:13.326
Please?

15:13.539 --> 15:15.746
Sorry, I would like to help you,

15:15.916 --> 15:18.669
but my feet are killing me
from all that dancing.

15:19.294 --> 15:22.462
Oh, why did we get rid
of that no-cancanning rule?

15:25.717 --> 15:26.881
Find another sucker.

15:27.094 --> 15:28.672
Since poker-playing
became legal again,

15:28.846 --> 15:29.961
I lost my saloon.

15:30.180 --> 15:33.383
And I am not leaving this table
until I win it back.

15:33.559 --> 15:36.264
Now, the cards with the people
on them are the good ones, right?

15:38.063 --> 15:39.309
Sorry, I can't help you.

15:39.481 --> 15:42.768
My shoulder's sore from shooting
all those sarsaparillas down the bar.

15:42.985 --> 15:44.563
Only got one good shoulder left.

15:45.112 --> 15:47.105
I understand.

15:47.698 --> 15:49.691
Of course I'll help you, sheriff.
It's my duty.

15:49.867 --> 15:52.275
After all those sugary sodas,
I got lots of energy.

15:52.494 --> 15:54.654
Finally. Thanks.

15:57.165 --> 15:58.542
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING]

15:58.709 --> 16:00.418
Train's here.

16:00.586 --> 16:03.588
The Petulant Kid. Okay.

16:03.755 --> 16:04.919
What am I gonna do?

16:05.090 --> 16:09.587
In the face of danger,
I'll just stand up and run.

16:14.391 --> 16:15.934
Giddyup.

16:16.101 --> 16:18.225
Trot. Amble.

16:18.395 --> 16:19.890
Any forward motion would be fine.

16:26.612 --> 16:29.982
Just you wait. There's a thing coming
called the internal combustion engine.

16:30.199 --> 16:32.192
Oh, boy. Look out, sheriff.

16:32.367 --> 16:34.859
It's the Petulant Kid.

16:39.082 --> 16:41.041
Okay, people,
now is when you dive for cover.

16:41.210 --> 16:44.911
Hey, I hear
you're the new authority in town.

16:45.881 --> 16:47.376
Okay, I get it.

16:47.591 --> 16:48.790
I'm the Petulant Kid.

16:49.009 --> 16:51.299
How ironic.
Oh, I'm my own worst enemy.

16:51.470 --> 16:52.669
Can I go home now?

16:52.846 --> 16:54.970
On the count of three, we draw.

16:55.432 --> 16:57.640
Uh-oh. Not armed. Duel's off.

16:57.851 --> 17:01.054
- Sheriff, catch.
- Oh, now you decide to be useful.

17:02.564 --> 17:04.807
Oh, a weapon with bad cuticles.

17:05.025 --> 17:06.354
- Dance.
- Me? No, thanks.

17:06.527 --> 17:08.152
Maybe later.

17:10.030 --> 17:11.691
Or now's good.

17:18.247 --> 17:19.445
This is gonna be fun.

17:20.082 --> 17:21.196
On the count of three.

17:21.415 --> 17:23.209
One, two...

17:23.417 --> 17:24.617
Three.

17:27.172 --> 17:30.174
I love when they run.
Makes it sporting.

17:31.802 --> 17:33.712
The Petulant Kid is after me.
Where can I hide?

17:33.887 --> 17:37.174
Don't worry.
I know exactly what to say to the kid.

17:40.227 --> 17:42.933
Take her, take her.

17:43.146 --> 17:44.227
Spare me.

17:44.439 --> 17:46.480
Oh, you manage to annoy me
in every genre.

17:53.740 --> 17:55.734
Well, that worked out very nicely.

17:57.119 --> 17:59.409
Perfect. An escape.

18:01.373 --> 18:02.453
I don't believe this.

18:02.624 --> 18:05.994
There should be a law against blocking
this alley with a chuck waggon.

18:06.420 --> 18:07.832
This is kind of awkward.

18:08.005 --> 18:09.381
Any last words?

18:09.548 --> 18:10.877
Yeah, I have a couple.

18:11.091 --> 18:14.093
The world needs rules to provide order
to protect us from ourselves,

18:14.303 --> 18:18.384
or life would be like a lawless,
chaotic frontier town.

18:18.599 --> 18:19.975
- Done?
- Yeah.

18:20.142 --> 18:23.263
- I was hoping that would end the spell.
- Wrong.

18:24.396 --> 18:25.939
Dad-blast it. I'm out of ammo.

18:26.148 --> 18:28.817
Really?
Well, I'm gonna count to three.

18:42.372 --> 18:45.374
That's not her horse, but I'll let it go.

18:46.168 --> 18:48.458
[CROWD CHEERING]

18:56.178 --> 18:58.255
Well, this is no longer
a lawless town.

18:58.472 --> 19:00.631
As sheriff,
I am reinstating all the rules.

19:00.933 --> 19:02.392
[CROWD CHEERING]

19:03.018 --> 19:06.269
Hey, hey, hey, no spontaneity
without written permission.

19:06.480 --> 19:08.058
Okay, maybe not all the rules.

19:08.273 --> 19:09.816
[CROWD CHEERING]

19:11.527 --> 19:14.778
And you were there,
and you were there, and you...

19:14.988 --> 19:17.065
Where the heck were you?
You I could have used.

19:17.282 --> 19:20.154
Sabrina, having you confront
your petulant self was our idea.

19:20.369 --> 19:21.745
But we got Jedediah to help us.

19:21.912 --> 19:23.537
He's very good
at this particular spell.

19:23.747 --> 19:25.373
Here.

19:25.541 --> 19:28.578
"Prospector,
teen rebellion squelcher, mohel"?

19:28.752 --> 19:30.580
You gotta diversify.

19:30.754 --> 19:32.415
Well, I certainly learned my lesson.

19:32.631 --> 19:33.711
Now if you'll excuse me,

19:33.882 --> 19:36.552
I have to go back to the coffeehouse
and try to grovel for my job.

19:36.718 --> 19:39.210
If you don't get it, come home,
you're still grounded.

19:39.721 --> 19:41.003
I can't wait for college.

19:41.223 --> 19:44.474
Once again, you have blurred the line
between civility and a police state.

19:47.604 --> 19:48.850
Very funny.

19:49.064 --> 19:51.473
Hi, could you scratch my back?

19:52.150 --> 19:54.109
Zelda!

19:54.862 --> 19:59.275
Okay, Jed, now that we've mined
all the magic, let's divvy it up.

19:59.449 --> 20:01.110
About that, it's gone.

20:01.326 --> 20:03.616
Gone, as in you're a dead man?

20:03.829 --> 20:07.032
Well, I used all of it
on that big old spell for Sabrina.

20:07.249 --> 20:10.370
Sabrina?
My magic went to Sabrina?

20:10.586 --> 20:12.994
Well, that's fair.
I mean, I've already got magic.

20:13.172 --> 20:14.999
No, that's Sabrina.

20:15.174 --> 20:16.503
But I'm a biped.

20:16.675 --> 20:18.384
No, that's Sabrina.

20:18.552 --> 20:19.632
But I can drive.

20:19.803 --> 20:21.002
No, I've done it again.

20:21.180 --> 20:22.461
That's Sabrina.

20:22.973 --> 20:25.180
I know what will make you
feel better.

20:28.520 --> 20:30.977
I don't need your pity or your--

20:31.440 --> 20:34.477
Cherry? My favourite.

